    <text id="B0551T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>How submit his ration reports, and explains why they are incomplete.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <abbr expan="Bureau">Bu.</abbr> &amp;c
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Colonel">Col.</abbr> O. Brown<lb/><abbr
                            expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst. Comr.</abbr><lb/>Richmond, <abbr
                            expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1865-12-16"><abbr expan="December">Dec.</abbr> 16th 1865</date>
                        <name type="place">Winchester</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Colonel</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have the honor to transmit herewith my Report of Rations Issued in the month of
                    November 1865.</p>

                <p>This report has been unavoidably retained for correction and is now incomplete in
                    not giving the values of the ration, because it could not be obtained from the
                    commissaries at Winchester and Staunton.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>I am &amp;c</salute>
                    <signed>W.S.H.<lb/><abbr expan="Captain">Capt</abbr> &amp;c</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
